cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper involves machine learning techniques applied to autonomous driving, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on Generative Adversarial Imitation Learning (GAIL) and Adversarial Inverse Reinforcement Learning (AIRL), which are both machine learning techniques. The second likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper involves decision-making in an autonomous driving context, which is a classic AI problem. The third likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper applies machine learning techniques to a robotics problem. The fourth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper may involve computer vision techniques for processing visual input from the driving environment. The fifth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper involves control strategies for autonomous driving.
